s, Bavaria, Germany","Öttingen, Schwaben, Bavaria, Germany":"Swabia, Bavaria, Germany","Öttingen, Donau-Ries, Bayern, Germany":"Donau-Ries, Bavaria, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Oettingen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hanni, Christoph, Siegbert.","German (also <b>Öttinger</b>): habitational name for someone from a place in Bavaria called Oettingen or a place in Lorraine (France) called Öttingen (French Ottange). Compare   Ottinger   and   Ettinger  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of   Ettinger  , a cognate of 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Ottinger","meanings":["German: variant of   Otting  .","German (also <b>Öttinger</b>): habitational name for someone from any of the places called Otting or Öttingen, in Swabia, Bavaria, and Lorraine (France). Compare   Oettinger  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of   Ettinger  , a cognate of 2 above."]}]},{"name":"Ludwig","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>hlud</i> ‘fame’ + <i>wīg</i> ‘war’; an ancient royal and imperial name.  See  <b>Louis</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Louis","meanings":["name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hlōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>wīg</i> ‘war’. It was very common in French royal and noble families.  Louis I  (  778–840 ) was the son of Charlemagne, who ruled as both King of France and Holy Roman Emperor. Altogether, the name was borne by sixteen kings of France up to the French Revolution, in which Louis XVI perished. Louis XIV, ‘the Sun King’ (  1638–1715 ), reigned for seventy-two years (  1643–1715 ), presiding in the middle part of his reign over a period of unparalleled French power and prosperity. In modern times Louis is also found in the English-speaking world (usually pronounced ‘<b>loo</b>-ee’). In Britain the Anglicized form   Lewis   is rather more common, whereas in America the reverse is true."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Wondrous’ or ‘enlightenment’.","2  ♀ ‘Fine jade’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Graf Ludwig II von Oettingen was born about 1140, in Oettingen, Oettingen in Bayern, Donau-Ries, Bavaria, Germany, his father, Ludwig I von Oettingen, was 12 and his mother, (Mädchen), was -4. He married Sofie von Lechsgemünd about 1190. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died before 28 June 1225."},"et":{"about 1140–before 28 June 1225":"umbes 1140–enne 28. juunit 1225","1140–1225":"1140–1225","1170–1242":"1170–1242","1190–1238":"1190–1238","1200–1279":"1200–1279","–1249":"–1249","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1146–Female":"1146–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1140":"umbes 1140","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1242":"1242","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","before 28 June 1225":"enne 28. juunit 1225","1170":"1170","1249":"1249","1238":"1238","1225":"1225","1279":"1279","1146":"1146","1200":"1200","UM 1165":"umbes 1165","Oettingen, Oettingen in Bayern, Donau-Ries, Bayern, Deutschland":"Oettingen, Oettingen in Bayern, Landkreis Donau-Ries, Bayern, Saksamaa","Öttingen, Schwaben, Bavaria, Germany":"Schwaben, Bayern, Saksamaa","Öttingen, Donau-Ries, Bayern, Germany":"Landkreis Donau-Ries, Bayern, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"about 1140–before 28 June 1225":"noin 1140–ennen vuotta 28. kesäkuuta 1225","1140–1225":"1140–1225","1170–1242":"